      "summary": "Attention U-Net for medical image segmentation (Oktay et al., MIDL 2018).",
      "extended": "A U-Net variant that inserts a soft **attention gate** on every skip\nconnection.  Each gate fuses the encoder feature $x^\\ell$ (the\n\"input\" branch) with the up-sampled decoder feature $g^\\ell$\n(the \"gating signal\") via\n\n$$\n\\alpha^\\ell = \\sigma\\!\\bigl(\\psi^\\top \\tanh(W_x x^\\ell + W_g g^\\ell)\\bigr),\n\\qquad\n\\hat{x}^\\ell = \\alpha^\\ell \\odot x^\\ell,\n$$\n\nsuppressing skip-feature activations outside the regions of interest\nhighlighted by the decoder.  This focuses the decoder's attention on\nrelevant anatomy and removes the \"noise\" carried over from encoder\nlayers — a consistent +1-3 Dice gain on medical-imaging benchmarks\nin the original paper.",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "config",
          "annotation": "AttentionUNetConfig",
          "description": "Frozen architecture spec.  Use `attention_unet` for the\nstandard 4-level configuration.",
          "default": null
        }
      ],
      "returns": null,
      "raises": [],
      "examples": [
        ">>> import lucid\n>>> from lucid.models.vision.attention_unet import attention_unet\n>>> model = attention_unet()\n>>> x = lucid.randn(1, 1, 256, 256)\n>>> out = model(x)\n>>> out.logits.shape   # (B, num_classes, H, W)\n(1, 2, 256, 256)"
      ],
      "notes": [
        "See Oktay et al., \"Attention U-Net: Learning Where to Look for the\nPancreas\", MIDL 2018 ([arXiv:1804.03999](https://arxiv.org/abs/1804.03999)).  The additive attention\ngate is identical to that of Bahdanau et al. (2015) generalised to\nfeature maps:\n\n\n\n$$\nq^\\ell = \\psi^\\top \\sigma_1\\!\\bigl(W_x x^\\ell + W_g g^\\ell + b_g\\bigr),\n\\quad\n\\alpha^\\ell = \\sigma_2(q^\\ell + b_\\psi),\n$$\n\nwith $\\sigma_1 = \\mathrm{ReLU}$, $\\sigma_2 = \\mathrm{sigmoid}$.\nThe intermediate channel count is typically half the input channels."
      ],
      "attributes": [
        {
          "name": "config",
          "annotation": "AttentionUNetConfig",
          "description": "Stored copy of the config that built this model."
        },
        {
          "name": "encoders",
          "annotation": "list[_EncoderBlock]",
          "description": "`config.depth` 2-D encoder stages (DoubleConv + MaxPool)."
        },
        {
          "name": "bottleneck",
          "annotation": "_DoubleConv",
          "description": "DoubleConv at the bottom of the U."
        },
        {
          "name": "decoders",
          "annotation": "list[_DecoderBlock]",
          "description": "`config.depth` decoder stages, each applying an attention gate\nto the corresponding skip feature *before* concatenating it into\nthe decoder DoubleConv."
        },
        {
          "name": "head",
          "annotation": "nn.Conv2d",
          "description": "1x1 convolution producing `num_classes` channels."
        }
      ],
