    {
      "name": "attention_unet",
      "path": "lucid.models.vision.attention_unet._pretrained.attention_unet",
      "kind": "function",
      "labels": [],
      "signature": "attention_unet(pretrained: bool = False, overrides: object = {})",
      "source": "https://github.com/ChanLumerico/lucid/blob/cbe1cd0ef/lucid/models/vision/attention_unet/_pretrained.py#L26",
      "subcategory": "pretrained",
      "summary": "Attention U-Net (Oktay et al., MIDL 2018).",
      "extended": "Builds an `AttentionUNetForSemanticSegmentation` with the\nstandard configuration: 4-level encoder / decoder, `base_channels =\n64` (channel schedule 64 -> 128 -> 256 -> 512 -> 1024),\n`in_channels = 1` (medical imaging default), and `num_classes = 2`.\nSoft attention gates on every skip connection suppress irrelevant\nencoder activations.",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "pretrained",
          "annotation": "bool",
          "description": "Reserved for future pretrained-weight loading.  Currently ignored.",
          "default": "False"
        },
        {
          "name": "**overrides",
          "annotation": "object",
          "description": "Keyword overrides forwarded into `AttentionUNetConfig`\n(`num_classes`, `in_channels` for RGB inputs,\n`base_channels`, `depth`, `bilinear`).",
          "default": "{}"
        }
      ],
      "returns": {
        "annotation": "AttentionUNetForSemanticSegmentation",
        "description": "Segmentation model with the standard Attention U-Net\nconfiguration applied (or with `overrides` merged on top of it)."
      },
      "raises": [],
      "examples": [
        ">>> import lucid\n>>> from lucid.models.vision.attention_unet import attention_unet\n>>> model = attention_unet(num_classes=4, in_channels=3)\n>>> x = lucid.randn(1, 3, 256, 256)\n>>> out = model(x)\n>>> out.logits.shape\n(1, 4, 256, 256)"
      ],
      "notes": [
        "See Oktay et al., \"Attention U-Net: Learning Where to Look for the\nPancreas\", MIDL 2018 ([arXiv:1804.03999](https://arxiv.org/abs/1804.03999)).  The defining attention-gate\nupdate is\n\n\n\n$$\n\\hat{x}^\\ell = \\sigma\\!\\bigl(\\psi^\\top\n    \\tanh(W_x x^\\ell + W_g g^\\ell)\\bigr) \\odot x^\\ell,\n$$\n\nwhere $x^\\ell$ is the encoder feature at level $\\ell$\nand $g^\\ell$ is the up-sampled decoder feature serving as the\ngating signal."
      ],
      "attributes": [],
      "warns": [],
      "see_also": [],
